20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65abdf3ddcdb354a98596b24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22641%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColossus.%3Cp%3EGCHQ%2FCrown%20Copyright%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EColossus%2C%20which%20was%20shrouded%20in%20secrecy%20until%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20was%20designed%20by%20engineer%20Tommy%20Flowers%20to%20decipher%20coded%20messages%20between%20some%20of%20Nazi%20Germany's%20most%20senior%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20helping%20the%20Allies%20win%20World%20War%20II.%20It%20provided%20critical%20intelligence%20that%20German%20leader%20Adolf%20Hitler%20had%20been%20duped%20into%20believing%20the%20Allies%20would%20invade%20occupied%20France%20via%20Pas-de-Calais%20rather%20than%20Normandy%2C%20where%20they%20would%20carry%20out%20the%20famous%20and%20pivotal%20D-Day%20landings%20on%20June%206%2C%201944%20%E2%80%94%20codenamed%20Operation%20Overlord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20huge%20machine%20was%20at%20the%20cutting%20edge%20of%20technology%20for%20its%20time%2C%20contained%202%2C500%20valves%2C%20and%20was%20a%20precursor%20to%20the%20computer%20age.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGCHQ%20said%20the%20images%20shed%20%26quot%3Bnew%20light%20on%20the%20genesis%20and%20workings%20of%20Colossus%2C%20which%20was%20over%20two%20meters%20tall%20and%20considered%20by%20many%20to%20be%20the%20first-ever%20digital%20computer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoldiers%20from%20the%20Women's%20Royal%20Naval%20Service%20(Wrens)%20were%20recruited%20to%20the%20large%20teams%20of%20operators%20and%20technicians%20needed%20to%20run%20and%20maintain%20Colossus'%20spy%20operation%20against%20Nazi%20Germany.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222476%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colossus.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65abdf9243bb77284b9ef56d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221857%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGCHQ%2FCrown%20Copyright%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBill%20Marshall%2C%20a%20former%20GCHQ%20engineer%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20computer%20during%20the%201960s%2C%20said%20he%20had%20to%20sign%20the%20%26quot%3BOfficial%20Secrets%20Act%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bwas%20told%20very%20little%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20machine%20he%20was%20working%20on%2C%20per%20GCHQ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20machine%20was%20actually%20doing%20was%20not%20for%20me%20to%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20until%20much%20later%20that%20I%20found%20out%20that%20the%20several%20of%20the%20systems%20and%20detailed%20design%20information%20were%20supposedly%20destroyed%20at%20the%20end%20of%20WWII.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20soldiers%20march%20up%20a%20hill%20after%20the%20D-Day%20landings%20in%201944%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F565457598430765c008b4f79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222418%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20march%20up%20a%20hill%20after%20the%20D-Day%20landings%20in%201944%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Herbert%2C%20a%20computer%20scientist%20who%20has%20served%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20Microsoft%20Research%20and%20is%20the%20chairman%20of%20trustees%20at%20The%20National%20Museum%20of%20Computing%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BColossus%20was%20perhaps%20the%20most%20important%20of%20the%20wartime%20code%20breaking%20machines%20because%20it%20enabled%20the%20Allies%20to%20read%20strategic%20messages%20passing%20between%20the%20main%20German%20headquarters%20across%20Europe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoused%20at%20the%20UK's%20code-breaking%20center%2C%20Bletchley%20Park%2C%2010%20Colossus%20computers%20helped%20550%20people%20decrypt%20%26quot%3B63%20million%20characters%20of%20high-grade%20German%20communications%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3