ded%20the%20Punjab.%20He%20was%20forced%20to%20turn%20back%20after%20his%20army%20suffered%20heavy%20losses%20in%20fighting%20Porus.%20Soon%20after%2C%20the%20Greek-ruled%20Seleucid%20Empire%20arose%20west%20of%20the%20Punjab%2C%20and%20the%20Mauryan%20Empire%20to%20its%20east%2C%20with%20its%20capital%20in%20Pataliputra.%20This%20produced%20a%20freer%20flow%20of%20ideas%20between%20India%20and%20Greece%2C%20as%20in%20science%2C%20art%2C%20and%20philosophy%E2%80%94and%20a%20fascinating%20account%20of%20India%20by%20Megasthenes%2C%20the%20Greek%20ambassador%20to%20the%20Mauryan%20court.%20Megasthenes%20described%20the%20huge%20city%20of%20Pataliputra%2C%20its%20wooden%20homes%2C%20walls%2C%20and%20watchtowers%3B%20its%20bureaucracy%2C%20taxation%20and%20laws%3B%20its%20giant%20army%3B%20urban%20lifestyles%2C%20elite%20fashions%20and%20social%20norms.%20He%20noticed%20the%20emergence%20of%20endogamy%20and%20early%20castes%20in%20the%20Aryanized%20groups%20around%20him%2C%20and%20he%20saw%20Brahminism%20as%20more%20patriarchal%20than%20Buddhism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ETwo%20generations%20later%20came%20Ashoka%20who%20presided%20over%20an%20expanding%20agricultural%20state%2C%20often%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20forest%20peoples.%20Still%2C%20his%20public%20embrace%20of%20non-violence%20in%20midlife%20was%20significant%20and%20likely%20unique%20among%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20emperors.%20He%20converted%20to%20Buddhism%20and%20sent%20missions%20to%20spread%20it%20far%20and%20wide.%20His%20public%20edicts%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20the%20earliest%20expressions%20of%20Indian%20secularism%2C%20in%20which%20the%20state%20attempts%20to%20fairly%20patronize%20all%20major%20religions.%20From%20the%20Mauryan%20period%2C%20we%20get%20monumental%20stone%20art%20and%20stunning%20sculpture%2C%20such%20as%20of%20Sanchi%20and%20Bharhut%20stupas%2C%20some%20with%20clear%20continuities%20with%20pre-Aryan%20forms%20and%20aesthetics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FEgY62P35WiA%3Fsi%3DfXWmHN6IKAhf9ffh%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFull%20transcript%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndians%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%E2%80%99m%20Namit%20Arora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20previous%20episode%20we%20looked%20at%20the%20coming%20of%20the%20Aryans%20and%20the%20Vedic%20Age.%20After%20centuries%20of%20ethnic%20mixing%20and%20migration%2C%20Indians%20once%20again%20developed%20a%20taste%20for%20cities%20and%20urban%20life%2C%20around%202500%20years%20ago.%20It%20produced%20a%20new%20age%20of%20social%2C%20intellectual%2C%20and%20religious%20innovation%2C%20and%20major%20cultural%20milestones%20like%20the%20Upanishads%2C%20the%20Buddha%2C%20Mahavira%2C%20the%20Carvakas%2C%20Panini%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlexander%E2%80%99s%20Invasion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EShortly%20after%20this%20came%20a%20major%20new%20force%E2%80%94the%20Greek%20invasion%20of%20the%20Punjab%20in%20326%20BCE.%20It%20was%20led%20by%20Alexander%20the%20Great%2C%20who%20came%20down%20the%20Khyber%20Pass%20with%20his%20army%20of%2050%2C000%20seasoned%20warriors.%20As%20he%20entered%20modern%20day%20Pakistan%2C%20king%20Ambhi%20of%20Taxila%20saw%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20and%20promptly%20surrendered.%20But%20another%20king%20challenged%20Alexander.%20His%20name%2C%20Porus%2C%20appears%20only%20in%20Greek%20sources.%20They%20fought%20a%20huge%20war%20by%20the%20river%20Jhelum.%20Alexander%20defeated%20Porus%20but%20suffered%20heavy%20losses.%20Impressed%20by%20Porus%E2%80%99s%20bravery%20and%20dignity%20in%20defeat%2C%20Alexander%20restored%20his%20kingdom%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThis%20encounter%20between%20Porus%20and%20Alexander%2C%20who%20is%20also%20known%20as%20Sikandar%20in%20India%2C%20has%20been%20depicted%20in%20Hindi%20cinema%20twice%2C%20in%20the%20films%20Sikandar%20in%201941%20and%20Sikandar-e-Azam%20in%201965.%20They%20captured%20the%20imagination%20of%20Indians%20by%20projecting%20modern%20nationalist%20passions%20into%20ancient%20settings%3A%20Porus%20was%20turned%20into%20a%20patriot%20defending%20Bharat%20mata%2C%20and%20Ambhi%20was%20declared%20a%20traitor.%20They%E2%80%99re%20best%20seen%20today%20as%20unintentional%20comedies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EEven%20though%20his%20army%20had%20shrunk%2C%20Alexander%20wanted%20to%20keep%20going%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20Ganga%2C%20but%20his%20troops%20rebelled.%20They%20had%20heard%20rumours%20of%20the%20Nanda%20Empire%E2%80%99s%20massive%20army.%20So%20Alexander%20reluctantly%20turned%20back%20from%20what%20is%20now%20Amritsar%2C%20and%20died%20on%20his%20way%20back%20to%20Greece.%20He%20was%20only%20in%20his%20early%2030s.%20After%20his%20death%2C%20his%20generals%20fought%20each%20other%20for%20territorial%20control%2C%20and%20set%20up%20independent%20kingdoms%20and%20empires%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanakya%20and%20Chandraguptra%20Maurya%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EA%20few%20years%20after%20Alexander%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20two%20people%20in%20the%20northwest%20got%20together.%20The%20first%20was%20a%20Brahmin%20called%20Chanakya%2C%20variously%20described%20as%20brilliant%2C%20ruthless%2C%20and%20devious.%20The%20second%20was%20an%20ambitious%20warrior%20called%20Chandragupta%20Maurya.%20Historical%20sources%20ascribe%20%E2%80%9Chumble%20origins%E2%80%9D%20to%20Chandragupta%2C%20suggesting%20that%20he%20may%20have%20been%20a%20Shudra.%20The%20two%20men%20forged%20alliances%20with%20other%20kings%2C%20assembled%20a%20large%20army%2C%20and%20fought%20a%20brutal%20war%20with%20the%20Nanda%20king%2C%20who%20ruled%20from%20Pataliputra%2C%20near%20Patna.%20Chandragupta%20won%20the%20war%20and%20established%20the%20Mauryan%20Empire%2C%20with%20its%20capital%20also%20at%20Pataliputra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMegasthenes%2C%20the%20Ambassador%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20dust%20settled%2C%20to%20the%20west%20of%20the%20Mauryan%20Empire%20was%20the%20Seleucid%20Empire%2C%20stretching%20from%20Afghanistan%20to%20Turkey.%20The%20Seleucid%20emperor%2C%20Seleucus%20Nicator%2C%20was%20Greek.%20As%20part%20of%20a%20peace%20treaty%20with%20Chandragupta%2C%20he%20offered%20his%20daughter%2C%20Helena%2C%20in%20marriage.%20Chandragupta%20sent%20back%20500%20elephants%20as%20a%20gift.%20Seleucus%20also%20sent%20Megasthenes%20as%20his%20ambassador%20to%20Chandragupta%E2%80%99s%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EMegasthenes%20has%20left%20behind%20a%20fascinating%20account%20of%20his%20time%20in%20India%2C%20even%20though%20parts%20of%20it%20are%20unreliable%20and%20seem%20outlandish.%20That%E2%80%99s%20because%20he%20seems%20to%20have%20written%20down%20both%20what%20he%20saw%20and%20what%20he%20heard.%20Sometimes%20he%20uncritically%20recorded%20tall%20tales%20that%20his%20native%20informants%20told%20him.%20Among%20these%20are%20absurd%20stories%20of%20people%20with%20bizarre%20physical%20features%2C%20like%20earlobes%20stretching%20down%20to%20their%20feet%2C%20men%20with%20only%20one%20eye%20on%20their%20foreheads%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20Megasthenes%20is%20much%20better%20on%20Pataliputra%2C%20where%20he%20stayed%20for%20at%20least%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20around%20300%20BCE.%20This%20part%20of%20his%20account%20is%20based%20more%20on%20his%20direct%20observation%20and%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMauryan%20Empire%20According%20to%20Megasthenes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ESo%20what%20did%20Megasthenes%20observe%3F%20He%20wrote%20that%20Pataliputra%20was%20a%20giant%20city%20located%20by%20the%20Ganga.%20It%20extended%2015%20km%20along%20the%20riverfront%20and%203%20km%20inland.%20Its%20size%20and%20population%20made%20it%20the%20largest%20city%20in%20the%20world.%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20very%20surprising%E2%80%94India%20had%20a%20relatively%20large%20population%20even%20back%20then%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20fertile%20plains%2C%20abundant%20rivers%2C%20and%20warm%20climate.%20Some%20estimates%20say%20the%20subcontinent%20then%20had%20about%2030%20million%20people.%20It%20then%20had%20a%20larger%20share%20of%20the%20global%20population%20than%20it%20does%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EBut%20here%20is%20an%20amazing%20factoid.%20Just%20since%20the%20Mauryan%20period%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20has%20grown%20SEVENTY%20times!%20Seventy%20times%20in%20about%20two%20thousand%20years.%20Imagine%20how%20empty%20it%20must%20have%20felt%20back%20then.%20It%E2%80%99s%20like%20the%20Mauryans%20lived%20in%20a%20different%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EMegasthenes%20tells%20us%20that%20much%20of%20Pataliputra%2C%20including%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20palace%2C%20was%20made%20of%20wood.%20This%20was%20not%20uncommon%20then%20for%20Indian%20cities%20located%20on%20floodplains.%20The%20city%20was%20surrounded%20by%20wooden%20walls%20and%20a%20moat.%20It%20had%20570%20watch%20towers%2C%20and%2064%20gates%E2%80%94averaging%20one%20gate%20every%20half%20a%20km.%20Archaeologists%20have%20found%20fragments%20of%20its%20wooden%20walls%20and%20a%20pillared%20hall%20of%20polished%20stone.%20But%20much%20of%20ancient%20Pataliputra%20is%20likely%20still%20beneath%20modern%20Patna%E2%80%94including%20what%20post-Mauryan%20dynasties%20later%20built%20in%20brick%20and%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWith%20the%20Mauryan%20empire%2C%20we%20see%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20bureaucratic%20state%2C%20with%20officers%20in%20charge%20of%20trade%2C%20taxation%2C%20roads%2C%20markets%2C%20births%20and%20deaths%2C%20population%20census%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20They%20catalogued%20people%20based%20on%20their%20occupations%20and%20taxed%20them%20differently.%20What%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear%20is%20how%20far%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20bureaucratic%20reach%20extended.%20The%20Mauryan%20Empire%20is%20conventionally%20shown%20as%20covering%20a%20huge%20area%2C%20but%20it%20included%20large%20autonomous%20regions%20where%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20state%20did%20not%20extend%20at%20all.%20Its%20actual%20sphere%20of%20influence%20may%20have%20been%20even%20smaller%20than%20in%20the%20map%20you%20see%20on%20the%20screen.%20It%20was%20likely%20based%20around%20a%20few%20urban%20centres%20in%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20such%20as%20Magadh%2C%20Gandhara%2C%20and%20Avanti.%20Much%20of%20India%20back%20then%20was%20forest%20land%2C%20where%20the%20locals%20hardly%20produced%20any%20surplus%20that%20an%20empire%20would%20want%20to%20control%20or%20tax.%20So%20it%E2%80%99s%20good%20to%20be%20sceptical%20of%20such%20evenly%20coloured%20maps%20of%20territorial%20unity%20or%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIn%20its%20urban%20zones%2C%20the%20Mauryan%20state%20was%20definitely%20a%20force%20to%20reckon%20with.%20It%20apparently%20had%20some%20aspects%20of%20the%20coercive%20authority%20and%20the%20surveillance%20regime%20described%20in%20the%20Arthashastra.%20This%20is%20a%20treatise%20on%20political%20statecraft%20attributed%20to%20Kautilya%2C%20who%20is%20often%20incorrectly%20equated%20with%20Chanakya.%20It%20was%20the%20work%20of%20multiple%20authors%20over%20centuries%20and%20is%20easily%20the%20most%20important%20work%20of%20political%20thought%20in%20ancient%20India%2C%20comparable%20to%20Aristotle%E2%80%99s%20Politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20Mauryan%20standing%20army%20was%20the%20largest%20India%20had%20ever%20seen.%20Megasthenes%20noticed%20that%20when%20the%20men%20of%20the%20army%20were%20not%20serving%2C%20%E2%80%98they%20spent%20their%20time%20in%20idleness%20and%20drinking%20bouts%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20royal%20treasury.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20land%20was%20fertile%20and%20enabled%20two%20harvests%20a%20year.%20People%20looked%20well%20fed%2C%20had%20a%20%E2%80%98proud%20bearing%E2%80%99%20and%20were%20%E2%80%98well%20skilled%20in%20the%20arts.%E2%80%99%20Theft%20was%20rare%20in%20Pataliputra.%20People%20often%20left%20their%20homes%20unguarded%20when%20they%20stepped%20out.%20Rich%20people%20wore%20expensive%20ornaments%20and%20fine%20cotton%20robes%20studded%20with%20gold%20work%20and%20precious%20stones.%20Polygamy%2C%20the%20practice%20of%20having%20more%20than%20one%20wife%2C%20was%20common%20in%20the%20upper%20class.%20Prostitution%20was%20legal%3B%20women%20in%20the%20profession%20were%20taxed%20and%20the%20state%20punished%20those%20who%20harmed%20them.%20Prostitution%20as%20a%20legal%20and%20taxable%20profession%20would%20remain%20common%20in%20Indian%20civilization.%20Many%20other%20foreign%20travellers%20noticed%20and%20wrote%20about%20it%2C%20as%20we%E2%80%99ll%20see%20in%20future%20episodes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20Mauryans%20built%20a%20road%20between%20Pataliputra%20and%20Taxila%2C%20a%20precursor%20to%20the%20Grand%20Trunk%20Road.%20A%20significant%20proportion%20of%20their%20trade%20and%20transportation%20also%20happened%20on%20rivers.%20But%20much%20of%20the%20Mauryan%20state%E2%80%99s%20revenue%20was%20tied%20to%20land%2C%20not%20so%20much%20to%20trade.%20Megasthenes%20wrote%20that%20people%20could%20not%20buy%20or%20sell%20land.%20Why%3F%20Because%20all%20land%20belonged%20to%20the%20crown.%20People%20could%20use%20the%20land%20but%20not%20own%20it.%20This%20would%20remain%20the%20dominant%20system%20in%20India%20through%20ancient%20and%20medieval%20times%2C%20with%20some%20variants%20and%20exceptions%20around%20religious%20land%20grants.%20Farmers%20typically%20paid%20a%20land%20use%20tax%20plus%20a%20produce%20tax.%20In%20Mauryan%20times%2C%20farmers%20paid%2025%25%20of%20their%20produce%20to%20the%20king%2C%20plus%20a%20sales%20tax%20of%2010%25.%20Tax%20dodgers%20were%20severely%20punished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EBut%20Brahmins%20and%20Buddhist%20monks%20had%20worked%20out%20a%20sweet%20deal%E2%80%94they%20were%20exempt%20from%20all%20taxes%2C%20whatever%20their%20income!%20This%20tax%20break%20to%20the%20priestly%20class%20would%20also%20become%20a%20persistent%20feature%20of%20Indian%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMegasthenes%20on%20the%20Animals%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EMegasthenes%20took%20great%20interest%20in%20the%20land%20animals%20and%20birds%20of%20India.%20He%20was%20Greek%20so%20elephants%20were%20especially%20exotic%20to%20him%2C%20and%20he%20was%20fascinated%20by%20them.%20He%20saw%20them%20often%20because%20the%20giant%20army%20of%20the%20Mauryan%20state%20had%20lots%20of%20elephants.%20He%20studied%20them%20carefully%20%E2%80%A6%20how%20they%20are%20captured%2C%20domesticated%2C%20used%20in%20war%2C%20and%20how%20their%20injuries%20are%20healed.%20He%20also%20wrote%20about%20a%20very%20interesting%20custom%3A%20When%20an%20elephant%20got%20angry%2C%20the%20Mauryans%20sang%20and%20played%20music%20before%20it%20to%20calm%20it%20down.%20Very%20much%20like%20the%20music%20therapy%20that%E2%80%99s%20offered%20nowadays%20in%20elephant%20sanctuaries%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20Megasthenes%20also%20marvelled%20at%20parrots%20who%20would%20become%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%98as%20talkative%20as%20children%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaste%20and%20Patriarchy%20as%20seen%20by%20Megasthenes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EMegasthenes%20noticed%20a%20peculiar%20kind%20of%20social%20hierarchy%20in%20India%2C%20in%20which%20endogamous%20groups%20were%20seen%20as%20high%20and%20low%E2%80%94especially%20among%20the%20speakers%20of%20Indo-Aryan%20languages%2C%20or%20Prakrits.%20He%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%98No%20one%20is%20allowed%20to%20marry%20out%20of%20his%20own%20group%20%E2%80%A6%20or%20to%20exercise%20any%20calling%20or%20art%20except%20his%20own%3A%20for%20instance%2C%20a%20soldier%20cannot%20become%20a%20herder%2C%20or%20an%20artisan%20a%20philosopher.%E2%80%99%20Clearly%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20free-wheeling%20division%20of%20labour%20but%20a%20division%20of%20labourers.%20What%20he%20had%20observed%20were%20not%20mere%20social%20classes%20but%20early%20castes.%20The%20spread%20of%20caste%20consciousness%20and%20patriarchy%20was%20then%20intimately%20tied%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20Indo-Aryan%20culture%2C%20and%20it%20was%20common%20enough%20in%20urban%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAlready%20in%20300%20BCE%2C%20Megasthenes%20had%20observed%20that%20Brahmin%20men%20guarded%20their%20religious%20knowledge%20and%20did%20not%20share%20it%20with%20men%20of%20other%20castes%2C%20or%20with%20women%E2%80%94not%20even%20their%20own%20wives!%20What%20the%20ambassador%20had%20observed%20was%20very%20real.%20A%20stark%20patriarchy%20is%20plainly%20evident%20even%20in%20the%20Brahminical%20texts%20whose%20early%20versions%20were%20being%20written%20at%20this%20time%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Manusmriti%20and%20Arthashastra.%20These%20texts%20demanded%20chastity%20from%20women%20and%20total%20obedience%20to%20their%20husbands.%20Women%20were%20largely%20relegated%20to%20domestic%20and%20maternal%20roles.%20But%20while%20Brahminical%20society%20created%20such%20restrictions%20on%20women%2C%20Megasthenes%20observed%20that%20women%20were%20free%20to%20pursue%20philosophy%20with%20the%20Sramanas%2C%20which%20included%20the%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%2C%20Ajivikas%2C%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20in%20Mauryan%20times%2C%20Brahminism%20had%20already%20become%20the%20leading%20driver%20of%20patriarchy%20in%20the%20subcontinent.%20And%20it%20was%20about%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20worse%20as%20endogamy%20spread.%20Upper-caste%20women%20had%20it%20worse%20because%20their%20sexuality%20had%20to%20be%20more%20strictly%20controlled%20to%20maintain%20the%20sanctity%20of%20caste%20and%20%E2%80%98purity%20of%20blood%E2%80%99.%20Even%20the%20roots%20of%20child%20marriage%20and%20the%20prohibition%20on%20widow%20remarriage%20lie%20in%20the%20peculiar%20logic%20of%20caste%20and%20endogamy.%20In%20the%203rd%20century%20BCE%2C%20all%20this%20was%20still%20in%20its%20infancy%20and%20affected%20only%20a%20small%20minority%20in%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20but%20it%20would%20steadily%20gather%20steam%20in%20the%20centuries%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndo-Greek%20Cultural%20Exchanges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAfter%20Alexander%2C%20there%20was%20a%20freer%20flow%20of%20ideas%20between%20East%20and%20West.%20Indians%20gained%20in%20science%E2%80%94such%20as%20astronomy%E2%80%94and%20in%20the%20arts%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20syncretic%20Greco-Buddhist%20art%20of%20the%20Gandhara%20school.%20In%20return%2C%20Indian%20philosophy%20influenced%20many%20schools%20of%20Greek%20philosophy%2C%20such%20as%20Neoplatonism%2C%20Stoicism%2C%20and%20Pyrrhonism%2C%20which%20was%20a%20school%20of%20philosophical%20scepticism%20that%20rejected%20dogma.%20The%20sceptical%20tradition%20was%20not%20only%20alive%20and%20well%20in%20India%2C%20it%20was%20even%20inspiring%20sceptics%20in%20Greece!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmperor%20Ashoka%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThree%20decades%20after%20Megasthenes%2C%20Ashoka%20became%20the%20Mauryan%20emperor.%20His%20story%20is%20now%20well%20known%2C%20but%20for%20centuries%2C%20Indians%20had%20completely%20forgotten%20him.%20His%20story%20was%20recovered%20through%20archaeology%20and%20non-Indian%20texts%20in%20modern%20times.%20As%20with%20so%20much%20of%20our%20history%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20probably%20best%20NOT%20to%20rely%20much%20on%20Bollywood%20to%20understand%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20life%20and%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWe%20now%20know%20that%20after%20a%20brutal%20war%20with%20Kalinga%2C%20Ashoka%20was%20pained%20by%20the%20suffering%20he%20had%20caused.%20His%20remorse%20led%20him%20to%20embrace%20Buddhism%20and%20its%20doctrines%20of%20nonviolence%20and%20compassion.%20By%20then%2C%20Buddhism%20had%20acquired%20a%20large%20urban%20following%2C%20though%20both%20Buddhism%20%26amp%3B%20Brahminism%20were%20still%20minority%20religions%20in%20the%20Subcontinent.%20That%E2%80%99s%20because%20most%20people%20still%20followed%20their%20animistic%20faiths%20and%20worshipped%20animals%2C%20trees%2C%20spirits%2C%20ancestors%2C%20and%20highly%20localised%20divinities%20of%20fertility%2C%20harvests%2C%20health%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EBut%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20urban%20subjects%20cared%20a%20great%20deal%20for%20Buddhism.%20So%20it%20was%20not%20a%20radical%20move%20for%20Ashoka%20to%20convert%20to%20Buddhism%2C%20or%20to%20send%20missions%20to%20spread%20it%20across%20India%20and%20beyond.%20Unlike%20Brahminism%2C%20Buddhism%20was%20a%20missionary%20religion%20equally%20open%20to%20all%20people.%20It%20devalued%20social%20hierarchies%20and%20held%20that%20everyone%20in%20the%20community%20had%20the%20same%20potential%20for%20spiritual%20attainment.%20At%20least%20in%20this%20respect%2C%20Buddhism%20was%20like%20Christianity%20and%20Islam%2C%20and%20this%20helped%20it%20gain%20followers%20across%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20Edicts%20Reveal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAshoka%E2%80%99s%20edicts%20reveal%20his%20benevolent%20yet%20stern%20paternalism.%20%E2%80%98All%20men%20are%20my%20children%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said.%20He%20urged%20them%20to%20lead%20pious%2C%20gentle%2C%20and%20virtuous%20lives.%20A%20politician%20saying%20such%20things%20today%20may%20seem%20to%20us%20overbearing%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20quibble.%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20personal%20inner%20transformation%20was%20rather%20impressive.%20He%20gave%20up%20armed%20conquest%20as%20part%20of%20his%20turn%20to%20nonviolence.%20He%20gave%20up%20hunting.%20He%20drastically%20cut%20down%20the%20killing%20of%20animals%20in%20his%20royal%20kitchen.%20He%20also%20made%20laws%20to%20reduce%20animal%20sacrifices%2C%20presumably%20by%20the%20Brahmins.%20He%20focused%20more%20on%20social%20welfare%2C%20as%20in%20building%20hospitals%2C%20tree-lined%20roads%2C%20and%20wells.%20He%20even%20made%20the%20treatment%20of%20prisoners%20more%20humane.%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20public%20embrace%20of%20non-violence%20was%20significant%20and%20likely%20unique%20among%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20emperors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ESome%20scholars%20believe%20that%20even%20Arjuna%E2%80%99s%20reluctance%20to%20join%20the%20war%20in%20the%20Mahabharata%20was%20a%20plot%20twist%20inspired%20by%20Ashoka.%20That%E2%80%99s%20quite%20plausible.%20Arjuna%20expresses%20his%20moral%20doubts%20about%20the%20war%20in%20the%20Bhagavad%20Gita.%20The%20Gita%20is%20of%20course%20a%20much%20later%20addition%20to%20the%20Mahabharata.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20as%20if%2C%20after%20Ashoka%2C%20the%20Brahminical%20class%20had%20to%20find%20retroactive%20justification%20for%20a%20war%20that%20also%20led%20to%20massive%20death%20and%20suffering%20in%20the%20epic.%20That%20justification%20is%20what%20Krishna%20tries%20to%20provide%20in%20the%20Gita%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20moral%20ambiguities%20about%20the%20war%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20epic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EHaving%20said%20that%2C%20we%20ought%20to%20keep%20things%20in%20perspective%20about%20Ashoka.%20There%20were%20surely%20gaps%20between%20his%20pronouncements%20and%20his%20practices.%20After%20all%2C%20he%20continued%20to%20maintain%20his%20armies%2C%20because%20can%20you%20run%20the%20business%20of%20empire%20without%20unnecessary%20violence%3F%20The%20empire%20had%20to%20grow%20by%20clearing%20forests%20for%20agriculture.%20Resistance%20and%20rivals%20had%20to%20be%20crushed.%20His%20rock%20edict%20%2313%20even%20issued%20a%20stern%20warning%20to%20the%20Adivasis%20of%20his%20day%2C%20asking%20them%20to%20behave%20or%20else%20be%20killed.%20These%20non-agricultural%20forest%20tribes%20were%20now%20part%20of%20a%20long%20and%20losing%20battle%20against%20expanding%20agricultural%20states%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAshokan%20%E2%80%98Secularism%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAshoka%20is%20interesting%20in%20another%20way.%20His%20public%20edicts%20can%20be%20called%20the%20earliest%20expressions%20of%20Indian%20secularism.%20In%20one%20edict%2C%20Ashoka%20claimed%20that%20he%20%E2%80%98honours%20all%20sects%20and%20both%20ascetics%20and%20laymen%2C%20with%20gifts%20and%20various%20forms%20of%20recognition.%E2%80%99%20He%20also%20said%20that%20anyone%20who%20glorifies%20his%20own%20faith%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20other%20faiths%20only%20damages%20his%20own.%20True%20religious%20merit%2C%20he%20said%2C%20comes%20from%20harmonious%20coexistence%20with%20people%20of%20other%20faiths.%20This%20sentiment%20is%20in%20line%20with%20what%20would%20later%20become%20the%20Indian%20ideal%20of%20secularism%2C%20in%20which%20the%20state%20does%20not%20separate%20itself%20from%20religion%20but%20attempts%20to%20patronise%20all%20major%20religions.%20Ashoka%20promoted%20this%20idea%20of%20an%20inclusive%20and%20secular%20state%2C%20long%20before%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98Indian%20secularism%E2%80%99%20came%20into%20being.%20Even%20for%20a%20small%20sect%20like%20that%20of%20the%20Ajivikas%2C%20he%20built%20the%20Barabar%20Hill%20Caves.%20In%20fact%2C%20Indian%20rulers%20have%20a%20long%20history%20of%20patronising%20multiple%20faiths%E2%80%94such%20as%20Ashoka%2C%20Kanishka%2C%20the%20Guptas%2C%20Harsha%2C%20the%20Palas%2C%20Akbar%2C%20and%20others.%20There%20are%20also%20counter%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Rise%20of%20Monumental%20Art%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20only%20from%20the%20Mauryan%20period%20in%20Indian%20history%20that%20we%20get%20monumental%20art%20and%20stunning%20sculpture.%20Examples%20here%20include%20the%20magnificent%20Sanchi%20Stupa%2C%20commissioned%20by%20Ashoka%20himself%20and%20augmented%20by%20others%20after%20him.%20Its%20intricate%20carvings%20include%20scenes%20of%20urban%20life%2C%20foreign%20visitors%2C%20animals%2C%20jataka%20tales%2C%20stories%20from%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20and%20much%20else.%20One%20can%20also%20see%20continuities%20with%20the%20art%20of%20the%20Harappans.%20The%20stupa%E2%80%99s%20beautiful%20art%20includes%20this%20dangling%20yakshi%2C%20with%20the%20same%20sort%20of%20mekhala%20belt%20around%20her%20hips%20that%20we%20saw%20in%20the%20Harappan%20female%20figurines.%20Many%20exquisite%20yakshi%20sculptures%20have%20been%20found%2C%20which%20seem%20to%20amplify%20the%20Harappan%20taste%20for%20curvaceous%20bodies.%20We%20see%20tantalising%20continuities%20in%20jewellery%2C%20ornaments%2C%20and%20headdresses.%20The%20origins%20of%20these%20voluptuous%20yakshis%20lay%20neither%20in%20Vedic%20Brahminism%20nor%20in%20Buddhism%2C%20but%20in%20folk%20religious%20cultures%20outside%20them%20both.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20were%20mostly%20rooted%20in%20non-Aryan%20belief%20systems.%20They%20represented%20popular%20goddesses%20of%20prosperity%20and%20fertility%2C%20such%20as%20Sri.%20Including%20such%20iconography%20on%20their%20religious%20monuments%20was%20a%20clever%20move.%20It%20made%20this%20new%20thing%20called%20Buddhism%20more%20palatable%20to%20the%20wider%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAshoka%E2%80%99s%20edicts%20on%20rock%20surfaces%20and%20sandstone%20pillars%20appeared%20throughout%20his%20empire.%20They%20were%20written%20in%20various%20Prakrits%2C%20and%20in%20Greek%20and%20Aramaic%20in%20the%20northwest.%20His%20officials%20probably%20read%20it%20aloud%20to%20a%20public%20that%20was%20still%20largely%20illiterate.%20One%20fine%20specimen%20is%20the%20lion%20capital%20at%20Sarnath%2C%20now%20the%20national%20emblem%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20India.%20I%20also%20love%20this%20head%20of%20a%20suave%20looking%20gent%20from%20the%203rd%20century%20BCE.%20I%20like%20his%20sardonic%20smile.%20Who%20knows%2C%20perhaps%20he%20belonged%20to%20a%20society%20of%20sceptics%20that%20may%20have%20inspired%20the%20Greeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EFinally%2C%20this%20folk%20goddess%20figurine%20from%20the%20Mauryan%20era%20reminds%20us%20of%20Harappan%20figurines%20like%20this%20one%2C%20with%20their%20ornate%20headdresses%20and%20ornaments.%20This%20clearly%20shows%20continuities%20in%20artistic%20tastes%20and%20conventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfter%20the%20Mauryas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAfter%20Ashoka%2C%20the%20Mauryan%20empire%20would%20fragment%20and%20shrink.%20The%20last%20of%20the%20Mauryas%20was%20murdered%20by%20an%20overzealous%20Brahmin%20named%20Pushyamitra%2C%20who%20was%20a%20Mauryan%20official.%20He%20then%20founded%20the%20Shunga%20Empire%20in%20Pataliputra.%20Scholars%20think%20that%20this%20was%20an%20orthodox%20Brahminical%20backlash%20to%20Mauryan%20rule.%20Pushyamitra%20hated%20Mauryan%20support%20for%20Buddhism%2C%20and%20he%20even%20persecuted%20Buddhists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EA%20fair%20bit%20of%20art%20from%20this%20period%20has%20survived.%20The%20eastern%20edges%20of%20the%20Shunga%20empire%2C%20where%20Indo-Aryan%20influence%20was%20weak%2C%20have%20left%20behind%20some%20remarkable%20art.%20Here%20are%20some%20examples%20from%20Bengal.%20They%20very%20much%20reveal%20a%20non-Aryan%20aesthetic%20of%20the%20human%20body%20and%20sexuality.%20We%20can%20see%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20realism%20and%20emotion%20in%20this%20art%2C%20and%20women%20are%20prominent%20in%20it.%20The%20subject%20matter%20is%20often%20secular%2C%20containing%20scenes%20from%20ordinary%20life.%20Amorous%20couples%20have%20started%20appearing%20on%20terracotta%20plaques.%20There%20is%20also%20some%20erotica%20from%20this%20period%20in%20Bengal%20that%20significantly%20predates%20later%20developments%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20India.%20At%20this%20stage%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20yet%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20temples%20or%20stupas%20but%20on%20small%20personal%20terracotta%20objects%2C%20such%20as%20plaques%2C%20vases%2C%20and%20other%20decorative%20art.%20These%20centuries%20also%20saw%20the%20maturation%20of%20the%20Jataka%20tales%20and%20the%20fables%20of%20the%20Panchatantra%2C%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20yoga%20sutras%2C%20Tamil%20Sangam%20poetry%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20northwest%2C%20the%20Indo-Greek%20states%20were%20replaced%20by%20the%20Sakas%20and%20then%20the%20Kushans%2C%20one%20of%20whose%20kings%20was%20the%20famous%20Kanishka.%20The%20sculpture%20of%20the%20Gandhara%20school%2C%20with%20its%20sublime%20Indo-Greek%20aesthetic%2C%20is%20perhaps%20the%20most%20visible%20legacy%20of%20this%20period.%20By%20then%20the%20Mathura%20school%20of%20art%20was%20also%20producing%20beautiful%20statues%20in%20its%20typical%20red%20sandstone.%20Some%20of%20the%20architectural%20marvels%20from%20these%20centuries%20include%20the%20Bharhut%20and%20Amravati%20stupas%2C%20and%20the%20many%20elaborate%20rock-cut%20caves%20of%20the%20Buddhists%20and%20Jains.%20On%20the%20social%20front%2C%20ideas%20of%20ritual%20purity%20and%20pollution%2C%20high%20and%20low%20caste%2C%20are%20evident%20in%20the%20literature%20of%20the%20period.%20The%20still%20evolving%20epics%20also%20embrace%20them.%20Many%20texts%20speak%20of%20despised%20jatis%20like%20chandalas%2C%20and%20of%20others%20involved%20in%20physical%20work%20like%20cleaning%2C%20basket%20making%2C%20hunting%2C%20fishing%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20A%20new%20hierarchical%20social%20order%20is%20well%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20next%20episode%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20turn%20my%20attention%20to%20south%20India.%20After%20the%20Mauryas%2C%20the%20big%20political%20entity%20there%20was%20the%20Satavahana%20Empire%2C%20alongside%20many%20smaller%20kingdoms.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20focus%20on%20the%20remarkable%20Ikshvaku%20kingdom%20and%20its%20capital%20city%20of%20Vijayapuri%2C%20located%20near%20Nagarjunakonda%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%20See%20you%20next%20time!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBibliography%2Ffurther%20readings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAllen%2C%20Charles%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAshoka%3A%20The%20Search%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20Lost%20Emperor%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Abacus%2C%202013%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDahlaquist%2C%20Allan%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMegasthenes%20and%20Indian%20Religion%3A%20A%20Study%20in%20Motives%20and%20Types%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Motilal%20Banarsidass%2C%201996%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEvans%2C%20James%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20History%20and%20Practice%20of%20Ancient%20Astronomy%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20OUP%2C%201998%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKeay%2C%20John%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndia%3A%20A%20History%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Harper%20Collins%20Publishers%2C%202000%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKulke%2C%20Hermann%2C%20Dietm