n%20Australia.%C2%A0The%20vast%20landmass%20was%20home%20to%20up%20to%20half%20a%20million%20people%20around%2070%2C000%20years%20ago%20but%20is%20now%20submerged%20around%20100%20meters%20deep.%20According%20to%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fplanet-earth%2Flost-atlantis-continent-off-australia-may-have-been-home-for-half-a-million-humans-70000-years-ago%5C%22%3ELive%20Science%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0this%20Australian%20%26quot%3BAtlantis%26quot%3B%20comprised%20a%20large%20stretch%20of%20continental%20shelf%20that%2C%20when%20above%20sea%20level%2C%20would%20have%20connected%20the%20regions%20of%20Kimberley%20and%20Arnhem%20Land%2C%20which%20today%20are%20separated%20by%20a%20large%20ocean%20bay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKasih%20Norman%2C%20an%20archeologist%20at%20Griffith%20University%20in%20Queensland%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20lead%20author%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0277379123004663%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%2C%20''We%20reveal%20details%20of%20the%20complex%20landscape%20that%20existed%20on%20the%20North%20West%20Shelf%20of%20Australia.%20It%20was%20unlike%20any%20landscape%20found%20on%20our%20continent%20today.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0277379123004663%5C%22%3EQuaternary%20Science%20Reviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20that%20the%20humans%20who%20lived%20there%20spoke%20similar%20languages%20and%20created%20similar%20styles%20of%20rock%20art%20to%20those%20living%20in%20the%20surrounding%20areas.%C2%A0It%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bvast%2C%20habitable%20realm%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bsingle%20cultural%20zone%26quot%3B%20with%20similarities%20in%20ground%20stone-axe%20technology%2C%20styles%20of%20rock%20art%2C%20and%20languages%2C%20as%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study's%20models%20show%20the%20continent%20or%20vast%20archipelago%20off%20the%20northwest%20coast%20of%20Sahul%20may%20have%20supported%20between%2050%2C000%20and%20500%2C000%20people.%C2%A0Sahul%2C%20the%20ancient%20land%20bridge%20comprised%20not%20only%20Australia%20but%20also%20New%20Guinea%20and%20Tasmania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20draw%20their%20conclusions%2C%20the%20researchers%20projected%20past%20sea%20levels%20onto%20high-resolution%20maps%20of%20the%20ocean%20floor.%20They%20found%20that%20low%20sea%20levels%20exposed%20a%20vast%20archipelago%20of%20islands%20on%20the%20Northwest%20Shelf%20of%20Sahul%2C%20extending%20500%20kilometres%20towards%20the%20Indonesian%20island%20of%20Timor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20ecological%20modelling%20reveals%20the%20now-drowned%20North%20West%20Shelf%20could%20have%20supported%20between%2050%2C000%20and%20500%2C000%20people%20at%20various%20times%20over%20the%20last%2065%2C000%20years.%20The%20population%20would%20have%20peaked%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20last%20ice%20age%20about%2020%2C000%20years%20ago%20when%20the%20entire%20shelf%20was%20dry%20land.%20Many%20large%20islands%20off%20Australia's%20coast%20%E2%80%93%20islands%20that%20once%20formed%20part%20of%20the%20continental%20shelves%20%E2%80%93%20show%20signs%20of%20occupation%20before%20sea%20levels%20rose%2C''%20the%20study%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20Ice%20Age%2C%20rising%20sea%20levels%20drowned%20the%20shelf%2C%20forcing%20its%20residents%20to%20flee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''Retreating%20populations%20would%20have%20been%20forced%20together%20as%20available%20land%20shrank.%20Rising%20sea%20levels%20and%20the%20drowning%20of%20the%20landscape%20is%20also%20recorded%20in%20the%20oral%20histories%20of%20First%20Nations%20people%20from%20all%20around%20the%20coastal%20margin%2C''%20researchers%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705814760000%2