A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705812832000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107024307%2Cimgsize-1550348.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fperu-president-grabbed-by-protester-at-public-event%2Farticleshow%2F107024190.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107024190.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20protester%20violently%20grabbed%20Peruvian%20President%20Dina%20Boluarte%20on%20Saturday%20during%20an%20event%20in%20the%20southern%20Ayacucho%20region%2C%20where%2010%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20mass%20anti-government%20demonstrations%20more%20than%20a%20year%20ago.%20TV%20footage%20of%20the%20assault%20showed%20Boluarte%20in%20traditional%20clothing%20surrounded%20by%20a%20crowd%20of%20people%20as%20she%20throws%20out%20candy%2C%20when%20a%20shouting%20woman%20approaches%20and%20grabs%20the%20president.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fperu-president-grabbed-by-protester-at-public-event%2Farticleshow%2F107024190.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fperu-president-grabbed-by-protester-at-public-event%2Famp_articleshow%2F107024190.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fperu-president-grabbed-by-protester-at-public-event%2Famp_articleshow%2F107024190.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Must%20Justice%20Have%20a%20Colour%3F%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192233%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000176B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinspired%E2%80%9D%20statement%20after%20visiting%20the%20temples%20at%20Dwarka%20and%20Somnath%20in%20Gujarat%20earlier%20this%20January%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20inspired%20this%20morning%20by%20the%20dhwaja%20at%20Dwarkadhish%20ji%2C%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20dhwaja%2C%20which%20I%20saw%20at%20Jagannath%20Puri.%20But%20look%20at%20this%20universality%20of%20the%20tradition%20in%20our%20nation%2C%20which%20binds%20all%20of%20us%20together.%20This%20dhwaja%20has%20a%20special%20meaning%20for%20us.%20And%20that%20meaning%20which%20the%20dhwaja%20gives%20us%20is%E2%80%93%20there%20is%20some%20unifying%20force%20above%20all%20of%20us%2C%20as%20lawyers%2C%20as%20judges%2C%20as%20citizens.%20And%20that%20unifying%20force%20is%20our%20humanity%2C%20which%20is%20governed%20by%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20by%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20dense%20statement%20with%20philosophical%20implications%20if%20connected%20to%20the%20future%20spirit%20of%20the%20law%20in%20India.%20There%20is%20a%20politics%20of%20mysticism%20behind%20the%20statement.%20The%20statement%20suggests%20that%20behind%20(and%20%E2%80%9Cabove%E2%80%9D)%20the%20force%20of%20law%20is%20another%20%E2%80%9Cunifying%20force%E2%80%9D.%20This%20force%20binds%20us%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eprior%20to%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0the%20force%20that%20binds%20us%20to%20the%20law.%20It%20is%20the%20force%20of%20national%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edhwaja%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20flag%2C%20in%20a%20temple%20represents%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20specific%20tradition%20within%20a%20nation.%20It%20does%20not%20represent%20all%20other%20traditions.%20The%20flag%20or%20any%20other%20symbol%20belonging%20to%20a%20tradition%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20universal.%20To%20consider%20tradition%20as%20part%20of%20sacred%20territory%20is%20still%20an%20argument%20of%20difference%2C%20distinguishing%20it%20from%20other%20traditions.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20mark%20of%20universality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUniversality%20is%20an%20idea%20connected%20to%20a%20secular%20culture%20(and%20a%20secular%20state).%20It%20does%20not%20represent%20any%20tradition.%20The%20principle%20of%20universality%20in%20a%20nation%20comes%20from%20the%20life%20that%20people%20of%20various%20cultures%20and%20traditions%20share%20together%20as%20citizens.%20Nehru%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Ca%20sense%20of%20common%20living%20and%20common%20purpose%E2%80%9D%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Discovery%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20meaning%E2%80%9D%20of%20traditions%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20become%20less%20special%20if%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20universal.%20Traditions%20are%20special%20precisely%20because%20they%20add%20to%20a%20nation%E2%80%99s%20diversity.%20To%20consider%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunifying%20force%E2%80%9D%20of%20tradition%20%E2%80%9Cabove%E2%80%9D%20all%20of%20us%20suggests%20that%20we%20are%20bound%20to%20a%20tradition%20before%20we%20are%20bound%20to%20any%20other%20idea%20or%20system%20of%20law.%20But%20the%20force%20of%20tradition%20can%E2%80%99t%20undermine%20the%20law%20of%20the%20state%20if%20that%20relationship%20has%20to%20be%20retained%20in%20any%20meaningful%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraditions%20are%20prejudicial%2C%20and%20their%20pretention%20to%20universality%20is%20circumscribed%20by%20prejudice.%20The%20profound%20prejudice%20of%20traditions%20governs%20the%20lives%20of%20people%20who%20swear%20by%20it.%20It%20also%20governs%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%20with%20others%2C%20those%20who%20do%20not%20belong%20to%20that%20tradition.%20The%20relation%20between%20traditions%20is%20governed%20by%20mutual%20prejudice.%20There%20are%2C%20however%2C%20ethical%20guidelines%20within%20traditions%20regarding%20how%20to%20relate%20to%20others%20outside%20it.%20These%20guidelines%20are%20part%20of%20the%20law%20of%20tradition%2C%20the%20tradition%20of%20law%20that%20predates%20the%20universal%20law%20of%20the%20secular%20state.%20These%20guidelines%20are%20still%20not%20universal%2C%20for%20each%20tradition%20understands%20its%20relation%20with%20others%20in%20distinct%20ways%2C%20connected%20to%20its%20own%20precepts%20and%20history.%20The%20ethical%20nature%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20traditions%20is%20derived%20from%20their%20mutual%20capacity%20to%20partake%20in%20shared%20life.%20The%20element%20of%20prejudice%20however%20persists%20in%20that%20relationship%2C%20and%20is%20often%20the%20cause%20of%20mutual%20animosity%20and%20strife.%20Justice%20in%20a%20secular%20nation%20is%20often%2C%20simply%2C%20the%20management%20of%20strife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPens%C3%A9es%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(1670)%2C%20Pascal%20identifies%20three%20sources%20behind%20the%20essence%20of%20justice%3A%20legislative%20authority%2C%20sovereign%20interest%2C%20and%20the%20surest%20of%20all%2C%20current%20custom.%20Justice%20is%20not%20eternal%2C%20but%20a%20matter%20of%20time.%20In%20his%20famous%20essay%20%E2%80%9COn%20Experience%E2%80%9D%20(1587-1588)%20Michel%20de%20Montaigne%20calls%20custom%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmystical%20foundation%20of%20authority%E2%80%9D%2C%20where%20he%20means%20to%20say%20that%20people%20follow%20the%20law%20not%20because%20it%20is%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejust%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(or%2C%20brings%20justice)%20but%20because%20they%20are%20laws%20to%20be%20obeyed.%20One%20obeys%2C%20or%20bound%20to%20obey%2C%20authority%2C%20even%20if%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just.%20Authority%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20collective%20belief%2C%20ruled%20by%20custom.%20Montaigne%20suggests%20that%20the%20customary%20nature%20of%20law%20prevents%20the%20possibility%20of%20imagining%20the%20just.%20It%20curtains%2C%20curtails%20justice.%20Does%20secular%20law%20overcome%20the%20constraints%20of%20custom%20to%20become%2C%20or%20realise%20itself%20as%2C%20universal%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejust%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%20Can%20this%20law%20become%20what%20Aniket%20Jaaware%20meant%20in%20his%20evocative%20phrase%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPractising%20Caste%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%C2%A0%3Cem%3EOn%20Touching%20and%20Not%20Touching%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20us%E2%80%9D%3F%20In%20his%20words%3A%20%E2%80%9CNot%20us%20and%20them%2C%20not%20you%20and%20me%20making%20up%20a%20divisible%20us.%20Just%20us.%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20is%20us%2C%20about%20us%2C%20the%20un%2Fjust%20us%2C%20the%20destitute%20of%20law.%20It%20is%20an%20undefinable%20us%20that%20cross%20the%20crisscrossed%20borders%20of%20traditions%20to%20seek%20what%20makes%20us%2C%20and%20what%20is%20denied%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%E2%80%99s%20statement.%20He%20not%20only%20invokes%20tradition%20but%20also%20%E2%80%9Cnation%E2%80%9D%2C%20equating%20the%20two%20to%20mean%20that%20there%20is%20a%20tradition%20of%20the%20nation%20that%20is%20symbolised%20and%20embellished%20by%20the%20dhwaja%20on%20the%20temple.%20The%20force%20of%20tradition%20binds%20both%20the%20giver%20and%20receiver%20of%20law%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20forms%20the%20essence%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20question%20arises%3A%20Does%20this%20force%20of%20tradition%20include%20the%20force%20of%20other%20traditions%3F%20In%20other%20words%2C%20can%20%E2%80%9Cuniversality%E2%80%9D%20be%20posed%20as%20an%20idea%20(and%20a%20value)%20within%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20name%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20the%20nation%20by%20not%20naming%20the%20diversity%20of%20traditions%20within%20it%3F%20Can%20the%20idea%2C%20or%20essence%2C%20of%20a%20singular%20custom%20become%20the%20unitary%20basis%20of%20the%20law%2C%20of%20that%20elusive%20possibility%20we%20call%20justice%3F%20Are%20%E2%80%9Clawyers%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cjudges%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccitizens%E2%80%9D%20together%20bound%20by%20a%20single%20tradition%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunifying%E2%80%9D%20source%20of%20our%20prejudicial%20authority%3F%20What%20if%20the%20idea%20of%20unity%E2%80%93%20proposed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cunifying%20force%E2%80%9D%E2%80%93%20does%20violence%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20diversity%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20not%20that%20traditions%20are%20eternal%2C%20immune%20to%20changes.%20They%20have%20evolved%20across%20time%20and%20undergone%20numerous%20improvisations%20through%20internal%20debates.%20Traditions%20are%20always%20in%20flux.%20The%20element%20of%20prejudice%20in%20traditions%20includes%20caste%20and%20gender.%20Nehru%20underlines%20modernity%E2%80%99s%20critical%20relationship%20with%20tradition%20succinctly%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Discovery%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CTraditions%20have%20to%20be%20accepted%20to%20a%20large%20extent%20and%20adapted%20and%20transformed%20to%20meet%20new%20conditions%20and%20ways%20of%20thought%2C%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%20new%20traditions%20have%20to%20be%20built%20up.%E2%80%9D%20Traditions%20are%20not%20sacrosanct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20flag%20belonging%20to%20a%20tradition%20also%20has%20a%20colour%20to%20it.%20Traditions%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20are%20also%20a%20display%20(and%20play)%20of%20colours.%20The%20colour%20of%20tradition%20is%20a%20singular%20colour%20within%20a%20diversity%20of%20colours.%20Can%20it%20also%20colour%20the%20law%3F%20Are%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20world%20(especially%20that%20of%20secular%20states)%20coloured%20by%20the%20mystical%20force%20of%20authority%3F%20The%20blind%2Fed%20figure%20of%20the%20law%20gives%20the%20impression%20that%20the%20law%20is%20also%20colourblind.%20Justice%2C%20we%20understand%2C%20has%20no%20colour.%20Is%20it%20just%20a%20foundational%20myth%20of%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20representation%20of%20itself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20end%2C%20I%20shall%20invoke%20a%20line%20from%20Jacques%20Derrida%E2%80%99s%20essay%20%E2%80%9CForce%20of%20Law%3A%20The%20Mystical%20Foundation%20of%20Authority%E2%80%9D%20(1994)%2C%20the%20force%20behind%20my%20meditation%3A%20%E2%80%9CTo%20address%20oneself%20to%20the%20other%20in%20the%20language%20of%20the%20other%20is%20both%20the%20condition%20of%20all%20possible%20justice.%E2%80%9D%20The%20ethical%20condition%20of%20modern%20(secular)%20law%20presupposes%20disputes%20between%20people%20following%20different%20customs%20and%20traditions%2C%20therefore%20different%20prejudicial%20authorities.%20In%20a%20similar%20manner%2C%20the%20law%20of%20the%20nation%20presupposes%20a%20society%20of%20minorities.%20The%20idea%20of%20unity%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ein%20this%20sense%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20presupposes%20the%20existence%20of%20diversity.%20It%20makes%20the%20law%20bound%20to%20the%20history%20(and%20possibility)%20of%20many%20customs%2C%20or%20traditions%2C%20that%20resource%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunifying%20force%E2%80%9D%20behind%20the%20idea%2C%20and%20spirit%2C%20of%20justice.%20The%20force%20of%20law%20of%20my%20tradition%20is%20paradoxically%20limited%20and%20expanded%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20force%20of%20law%20of%20the%20other%20who%20belongs%20to%20another%20tradition.%20It%20is%20the%20other%20that%20brings%20the%20fundamental%20predicament%20to%20law%20and%20justice%3A%20How%20to%20be%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejust%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0to%20what%20is%20prior%20to%20%E2%80%93%20and%20yet%20becomes%20the%20basis%20of%E2%80%93%20unity%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20must%20arbiter%20between%20our%20mutual%20prejudices.%20It%20must%20be%20above%20what%20limits%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20writer%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3ENehru%20and%20the%20Spirit%20of%20India%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0He%20is%20working%20on%20a%20book%20on%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705812284000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192233%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000176B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmust-justice-have-a-colour%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20law%20must%20arbiter%20between%20our%20mutual%20prejudices.%20It%20must%20be%20above%20what%20limits%20us.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22