m%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ffresh-formal-job-creation-dipped-to-30-month-low-levels-in-nov-epfo-124012000548_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Backstory%3A%26nbsp%3BThe%20Temple%20Template%20and%20How%20the%20Indian%20Media%20Has%20Learnt%20to%20Conform%20to%20It%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08152830%2F415251923_1140688907425340_6473205362871466006_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJanuary%2022%20will%20mark%20a%20portentous%20moment%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20country%20when%20the%20head%20of%20its%20government%20will%20emerge%20wearing%20two%20headgear%3A%20one%20signifying%20his%20constitutional%20status%20as%20the%20chief%20head%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20a%20Sovereign%2C%20Secular%20India%3B%20the%20other%20as%20the%20chief%20%E2%80%98yajman%E2%80%99%20(main%20host)%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Epran%20pratishtha%3C%2Fem%3E%20rituals%20that%20will%20accompany%20the%20consecration%20of%20the%20idol%20of%20Lord%20Ram%20in%20the%20specially%20constructed%2C%20if%20far%20from%20complete%2C%20Ram%20Mandir%20at%20Ayodhya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20multiple%20ironies%20inherent%20in%20this%20elaborately%20constructed%2C%20richly%20embellished%20tableau%20seem%20to%20have%20thus%20far%20escaped%20the%20attention%20of%20mainstream%20media.%20Or%20is%20it%20the%20case%20that%20since%20that%20fateful%20day%20of%20December%206%2C%201992%2C%20when%20the%20domes%20of%20an%20ancient%20mosque%20were%20brought%20down%2C%20the%20Indian%20media%20have%20been%20systematically%20divesting%20themselves%20of%20their%20secular%20legacy%3F%20The%20argument%20could%20be%20made%20that%20mainstream%20media%20actually%20enabled%20the%20emergence%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20in%20significant%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20altered%20the%20public%20narrative%20regarding%20it.%20Early%20media%20references%20in%20the%201980s%20were%20framed%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Babri%20Masjid-Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20dispute%E2%80%99.%20The%20actual%20demolishing%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20when%20it%20happened%2C%20had%20already%20been%20preceded%20by%20a%20verbal%20diminution%20of%20the%20mosque%20in%20media%20conversations.%20The%20words%20%E2%80%98Babri%20Masjid%E2%80%99%20came%20to%20be%20replaced%20over%20time%20by%20the%20formulation%20%E2%80%98disputed%20structure%E2%80%99.%20Once%20the%20%E2%80%98disputed%20structure%E2%80%99%20was%20reduced%20to%20rubble%20and%20dust%20in%201992%2C%20it%20was%20the%20temple%2C%20not%20the%20mosque%20that%20gained%20media%20coverage.%20Calls%20to%20rebuild%20the%20mosque%20were%20feeble%20while%20the%20temple%20took%20on%20an%20afterlife%20once%20the%20Ram%20idol%20was%20safely%20housed%20in%20a%20tent%20pitched%20on%20the%20debris%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20with%20a%20new%20term%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98makeshift%20temple%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20used%20to%20signify%20its%20live%20status.%20In%20time%20it%20only%20grew%20in%20the%20public%20imagination%20with%20much%20coverage%20devoted%20to%20the%20crowds%20that%20routinely%20gathered%20to%20worship%20there.%20The%20media%20now%20began%20to%20use%20another%20useful%20phrase%20%E2%80%93%20a%20%E2%80%98matter%20of%20faith%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20the%20tarpaulin%20to%20cover%20all%20manner%20of%20historical%20distortions%2C%20fake%20discoveries%2C%20and%20cynically%20manufactured%20irrationalities%2C%20including%20of%20course%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmiraculous%20appearance%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20idol%20within%20the%20mosque%20on%20the%20night%20of%20December%2022%2C%201949.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11120348%2FPrime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_performing_Bhoomi_Pujan_at_%25E2%2580%2598Shree_Ram_Janmabhoomi_Mandir%25E2%2580%2599_in_Ayodhya_Uttar_Pradesh_on_August_05_2020.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11120348%2FPrime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_performing_Bhoomi_Pujan_at_%25E2%2580%2598Shree_Ram_Janmabhoomi_Mandir%25E2%2580%2599_in_Ayodhya_Uttar_Pradesh_on_August_05_2020.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11120348%2FPrime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_performing_Bhoomi_Pujan_at_%25E2%2580%2598Shree_Ram_Janmabhoomi_Mandir%25E2%2580%2599_in_Ayodhya_Uttar_Pradesh_on_August_05_2020-300x184.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11120348%2FPrime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_performing_Bhoomi_Pujan_at_%25E2%2580%2598Shree_Ram_Janmabhoomi_Mandir%25E2%2580%2599_in_Ayodhya_Uttar_Pradesh_on_August_05_2020-1024x627.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692406%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22735%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20performing%20bhoomi%20pujan%20at%20Ram%20Mandir.%20Also%20visible%20are%20Mohan%20Bhagwat%20and%20Anandiben%20Patel.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20election%20campaign%20of%20the%202014%20general%20election%20had%20references%20to%20Lord%20Ram.%20In%20May%2C%20just%20before%20his%20electoral%20success%2C%20newspapers%20reported%20him%20sitting%20against%20a%20portrait%20of%20the%20deity%2C%20exhorting%20the%20people%20of%20Ayodhya%20to%20defeat%20the%20Congress.%20But%20what%20really%20brought%20the%20temple%20to%20the%20front%20and%20centre%20of%20politics%20was%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20of%20November%209%2C%202019%2C%20after%20Modi%20won%20his%20second%20stint%20in%20office.%20It%20came%20in%20extremely%20well-crafted%20language%20and%20gestured%20ostentatiously%20towards%20Constitutional%20values%20that%20recognised%20the%20equality%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccitizens%20of%20all%20faiths%2C%20beliefs%20and%20creeds%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20concluding%20words%20should%20remain%20etched%20in%20our%20collective%20memory%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20facts%2C%20evidence%20and%20oral%20arguments%20of%20the%20present%20case%20have%20traversed%20the%20realms%20of%20history%2C%20archaeology%2C%20religion%20and%20the%20law.%20The%20law%20must%20stand%20apart%20from%20political%20contestations%20over%20history%2C%20ideology%20and%20religion%E2%80%A6.we%20must%20remember%20that%20it%20is%20the%20law%20which%20provides%20the%20edifice%20upon%20which%20our%20multicultural%20society%20rests%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20Having%20stated%20that%2C%20the%20verdict%20went%20on%20to%20demolish%20that%20edifice%20and%20hand%20over%20the%20disputed%202.77%20acres%20of%20land%20on%20which%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20had%20once%20stood%20to%20the%20Central%20government%20to%20be%20maintained%20by%20the%20government%20or%20any%20person%20or%20trust%20it%20seeks%20to%20set%20up%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20again%20the%20media%20failed%20to%20adequately%20call%20out%20the%20hypocrisies%20of%20that%20verdict.%20The%20call%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20review%20this%20judgment%20should%20have%20come%20from%20the%20media%20but%20instead%2C%20it%20came%20from%20a%20group%20of%20civil%20society%20actors%20who%20issued%20a%20public%20statement%20detailing%20their%20concern.%20It%20pointed%20out%20the%20foundational%20truth%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20itself%20has%20been%20made%20possible%20only%20by%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20criminal%20destruction%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20court%20could%20not%20have%20handed%20over%20the%20site%20to%20the%20Hindu%20side%20if%20the%20mosque%20was%20still%20standing.%C2%A0%20It%20also%20critiqued%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccavalier%20and%20one-sided%E2%80%9D%20way%20in%20which%20the%20Court%20dealt%20with%20both%20archaeology%20and%20history%2C%20even%20overlooking%20Tulsidas%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20the%20site%20being%20Rama%E2%80%99s%20birthplace.%20Finally%20came%20the%20trenchant%20observation%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Court%E2%80%99s%20assigning%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20the%20task%20of%20setting%20up%20a%20Hindu%20religious%20trust%20to%20build%20the%20future%20Rama%20temple%20on%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20site%20implies%20that%20in%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20it%20is%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20duty%20to%20cater%20to%20Hindu%20religious%20interests.%20This%20surely%20is%20hardly%20in%20consonance%20with%20the%20supposed%20secular%20nature%20of%20our%20state.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20court%20judgment%20providing%20the%20cover%20of%20legitimacy%20to%20the%20entire%20exercise%2C%20it%20was%20now%20easy%20for%20television%20channels%20and%20major%20newspapers%20to%20finally%20lay%20to%20rest%20any%20lingering%20qualms%20they%20may%20have%20had%20over%20promoting%20the%20Ayodhya%20temple.%20The%20coverage%20of%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20overseeing%20the%20shifting%20of%20the%20Ram%20Lalla%20idol%20from%20the%20makeshift%20temple%20to%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20site%20in%20March%202020%20was%20ecstatic%20despite%20the%20pandemic%20having%20the%20country%20in%20its%20grip.%C2%A0%20In%20August%20of%20that%20year%2C%20while%20the%20pandemic%20was%20still%20raging%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20performed%20the%20groundbreaking%20ceremony%20for%20the%20temple.%C2%A0%20A%20new%20religiosity%20entered%20the%20reportage.%20The%20fact%20that%20he%20prostrated%20before%20the%20Ram%20idol%2C%20not%20once%20but%20thrice%2C%20was%20duly%20noted%20and%20photographs%20of%20it%20were%20splashed%20all%20over%20the%20media%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20began%20to%20systematically%20build%20up%20the%20prime%20minister%20as%20a%20quasi-spiritual%20figure.%20Today%20the%20arc%20of%20that%20narrative%20has%20come%20full%20circle%2C%20with%20cutouts%20of%20Modi%20seen%20cheek-by-jowl%20with%20cut-outs%20of%20Lord%20Ram.%20All%20the%20major%20newspapers%20have%20faithfully%20reported%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9C73-year-old%20was%20sleeping%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20consuming%20only%20coconut%20water%E2%80%9D%20to%20prepare%20himself%20for%20the%20ceremonies%20that%20he%20will%20be%20performing%20as%20chief%20%E2%80%98yajman%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20spiritual%20acts%20have%20strong%20political%20and%20electoral%20intent.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20and%20his%20party%20need%20a%20constant%20supply%20of%20such%20photos.%20The%20photo%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20consecrating%20%E2%80%98Ram%20Lalla%E2%80%99%20in%20Ayodhya%20will%20promote%20Modi%20as%20the%20civilisational%20man%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98king%E2%80%99%20who%20brought%20Ram%20back%20home%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-january-22-ram-temple-inauguration-is-a-political-event-its-a-crucial-test-for-indian-politics%5C%22%3EThe%20January%2022%20Ram%20Temple%20Inauguration%20Is%20a%20Political%20Event.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20Crucial%20Test%20for%20Indian%20Politics%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20January%2010).%20And%20indeed%20triumphalist%20headlines%20like%20%E2%80%98Lord%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20Grand%20Return%20to%20Ayodhya%20Temple%20After%20500-Year%20Struggle%E2%80%99%20now%20flash%20out%20on%20front%20pages%20and%20prime-time%20television%20shows.%20With%20a%20half-holiday%20announced%20on%20January%2022%2C%20the%20attempt%20is%20now%20to%20present%20it%20as%20a%20new%20independence%20day%20for%20India.%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20famed%20formulation%2C%20%E2%80%98Tryst%20with%20Destiny%E2%80%99%2C%20once%20deeply%20entwined%20with%20Independence%20Day%201947%2C%20is%20now%20being%20put%20to%20service%20in%20Ayodhya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20government%20will%20pull%20all%20stops%20to%20keep%20this%20mediatised%20euphoria%20going%20at%20least%20until%20counting%20day%202024.%20Meanwhile%2C%20for%20many%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20fractious%20history%20behind%20the%20mandir%20moment%20comes%20rife%20with%20memories%2C%20not%20of%20the%20Independence%20Movement%2C%20but%20of%20Partition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%2B%2B%2B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBroadcasting%20Services%20Bill%3A%20Regulation%20as%20Control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2010%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20(MIB)%20put%20out%20a%20notice%20on%20its%20website%20seeking%20responses%20from%20the%20public%20and%20media%20stakeholders%20on%20its%20new%20draft%20%E2%80%98Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%2C%202023%E2%80%99.%20It%20described%20the%20Bill%20in%20a%20strikingly%20anodyne%20fashion%20as%20one%20that%20caters%20%E2%80%9Cto%20the%20evolving%20needs%20of%20the%20Broadcasting%20sector%2C%20which%20when%20it%20is%20enacted%20will%20replace%20the%20existing%20Cable%20Television%20Network%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%201995.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20invitation%20drew%20a%20wide%20and%20engaged%20response%20from%20%E2%80%9Cstakeholders%E2%80%9D%2C%20ranging%20from%20concerned%20individuals%20to%20a%20slew%20of%20internet%20and%20media%20bodies%2C%20most%20of%20them%20expressing%20alarm%20over%20what%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20broaden%20and%20deepen%20State%20control%20over%20the%20media%20space%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20case%20the%20%E2%80%98Over-the-Top%E2%80%99%20or%20OTT%20content%20and%20digital%20news%20portals%20run%20by%20companies%20and%20individual%20journalists.%20The%20last%20few%20years%20has%20seen%20this%20sector%20emerge%20as%20a%20particularly%20vibrant%20space%20and%20today%20the%20new%20Bill%20hangs%20like%20a%20Damocles%20Sword%20over%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20the%20responses%20to%20it%2C%20the%20Bill%20crosses%20several%20red%20lines.%20The%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%2C%20with%20its%20zany%20campaign%20slogan%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Dear%20MIB%2C%20kill%20the%20bill%20and%20%23LetUsChill%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20considerably%20bolstered%20up%20the%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20overriding%20concerns%20that%20jump%20out%20of%20the%20page%20is%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20enhances%20the%20capacity%20for%20subjective%20interpretation%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20regulator.%20The%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20observes%3A%20%E2%80%9CAmbiguous%20definitions%2C%20uncertainty%20over%20scope%20of%20application%2C%20and%20reliance%20on%20future%20rulemaking%20by%20the%20executive%20makes%20the%20Broadcasting%20Bill%20vague%2C%20overbroad%2C%20and%20worrisome%2C%20that%20is%20open%20for%20misuse%20through%20subjective%20and%20selective%20application.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20disturbing%20history%20of%20such%20legislation%2C%20as%20Simran%20Agarwal%20and%20Shubhangi%20Heda%20point%20out%20in%20%E2%80%98Media%20Regulations%20in%20India%3A%20Government%20Overreach%20Disguised%20as%20%E2%80%98Parity%E2%80%99%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20To%20bring%20about%20regulatory%20parity%20across%20media%20industries%2C%20they%20pointed%20out%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%E2%80%99s%20interventions%20in%20the%20media%20space%20have%20taken%20two%2C%20often%20simultaneous%2C%20routes.%20One%2C%20the%20adoption%20of%20an%20umbrella%20regulatory%20approach%20(as%20for%20instance%20when%20the%20Telecommunication%20Act%20replaced%20the%20Indian%20Telegraph%20Act%2C1885%3B%20the%20Indian%20Wireless%20Telegraphy%20Act%2C1933%3B%C2%A0%20and%20The%20Telegraph%20Wire%20(Unlawful%20Protection)%20Act%2C%201950).%20The%20second%20route%20is%20to%20mix%20old%20and%20new%20forms%20of%20regulations%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20align%20newer%20media%20systems%20with%20earlier%20regulatory%20mechanisms%2C%20while%20also%20attempting%20to%20introduce%20novel%2C%20and%20technology-conscious%20provisions%20into%20existing%20frameworks.%20Such%20retrofitting%20is%20fraught%20with%20dangers.%20DeepStrat%2C%20a%20strategic%20consultancy%20based%20out%20of%20Delhi%2C%20in%20fact%20pointed%20out%20that%20since%20OTT%20services%20operate%20differently%20than%20broadcasting%20services%2C%20they%20must%20never%20be%20regulated%20in%20the%20same%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeema%20Chisti%2C%20editor%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.in%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CThe%20idea%20is%20to%20give%20enough%20room%20in%20the%20clauses%20to%20hustle%20every%20kind%20of%20animal%20into%20the%20tent.%20OTT%2C%20those%20doing%20video%20online%2C%20those%20reposting%20it%2C%20forwarding%20content%20are%20covered%E2%80%A6The%20writing%20is%20suitably%20vague%20to%20not%20be%20restricted%20to%20a%20reference%20to%20just%20captions%20or%20astons%20on%20audio-visual%2C%20but%20%E2%80%98writing%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20what%20you%20are%20reading%20now.%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3EControl%20%2B%20All%20or%20Delete%3A%20The%20Draft%20Broadcast%20Bill%20Is%20a%20Blueprint%20for%20Censorship%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.in%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20December%207).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20statement%2C%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20examined%20the%20architecture%20of%20regulation%20in%20the%20Bill%20and%20feared%20that%20it%20left%20entities%20which%20come%20under%20its%20ambit%20at%20%E2%80%9Crisk%20of%20being%20influenced%20by%20political%20and%20industrial%20pressure%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Media%20Foundation%2C%20in%20its%20recommendations%2C%20specifically%20pointed%20to%20how%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunprecedented%20regulatory%20bodies%20being%20proposed%20in%20the%20Bill%20pose%20a%20risk%20of%20being%20influenced%20by%20political%20and%20industrial%20pressure.%20This%20might%20lead%20to%20mistrust%20of%20these%20bodies%20amongst%20the%20OTT%20services%20which%20might%20increase%20the%20chances%20of%20self-censorship.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%2C%20on%20its%20part%2C%20termed%20the%20regulatory%20structure%20%E2%80%9Cretrograde%E2%80%9D.%20It%20observes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20third-tier%20in%20the%20regulatory%20structure%2C%20unreasonable%20reliance%20on%20future%20rulemaking%20powers%2F%20delegated%20legislation%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20inspection%20and%20penalty%20provisions%20(such%20as%20to%20prohibit%20operation%20in%20public%20interest)%2C%20create%20a%20skewed%20power%20dynamic%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20Bill%20could%20well%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20blueprint%20for%20future%20pre-censorship%2C%20as%20Chisti%20points%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20egregious%20over-reach%20in%20the%20draft%20is%20the%20clubbing%20of%20news%20(independent%20news%20websites%2C%20individuals%20now%20established%20as%20popular%20points%20for%20news%20and%20views%2C%20explainer%20videos%2C%20other%20audio-visual%20material%20available%20online)%20with%20OTT%20content%2C%20shows%2C%20serials%2C%20documentaries%20and%20other%20features%20traditionally%20subject%20to%20a%20certification%20norm.%20By%20introducing%20this%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98combo-pack%E2%80%99%20as%20Jawhar%20Sircar%2C%20an%20ex-CEO%20of%20Prasar%20Bharti%20puts%20it%2C%20news%20for%20the%20first%20time%20is%20being%20put%20into%20a%20Central%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification%20or%20CBFC%20inspired%20regime%20reserved%20for%20cinema.%20These%20are%20the%20first%20steps%20to%20establish%20a%20blueprint%20for%20pre-censorship.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stipulations%20in%20the%20Bill%20lead%20inevitably%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20financial%20and%20compliance%20burden%3A%20punishment%20could%20come%20in%20the%20form%20of%20suspension%2C%20expulsions%2C%20and%20hefty%20fines.%C2%A0%20These%20in%20themselves%20could%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20quietly%20allows%20seizure%20of%20journalists%E2%80%99%20devices%20by%20regulatory%20authorities%2C%20something%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20expressed%20strong%20reservations%20over%20last%20November.%20DeepStrat%20points%20out%2C%20as%20do%20several%20others%20in%20their%20submissions%2C%20that%20Clause%2031%20of%20the%20Bill%20which%20greenlights%20such%20seizure%20needs%20to%20be%20re-evaluated%20%E2%80%9Cconsidering%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20granting%20authorised%20officers%20the%20power%20to%20seize%20broadcasting%20equipment%20based%20on%20%E2%80%98reason%20to%20believe%E2%80%99.%20Such%20broad%20powers%20pose%20threats%20to%20procedural%20fairness%2C%20operational%20continuity%2C%20and%20potential%20misuse%20of%20authority.%E2%80%9D%20It%20could%20also%20lead%20to%20unjustified%20disruptions%20for%20broadcasters%20without%20a%20transparent%20investigation%2C%20it%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20concludes%20quite%20rightly%20that%20%E2%80%9CGiven%20MIB%E2%80%99s%20historical%20baggage%20with%20paternalistic%20regulation%2C%20moral%20policing%2C%20and%20censorship%20of%20curated%20content%20as%20well%20as%20news%20media%2C%20this%20bill%20may%20very%20well%20alter%20the%20digital%20space%2C%20for%20creators%20and%20consumers%20alike.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2B%2B%2B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndian%20journalists%20behind%20bars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJournalism%20is%20not%20a%20crime%2C%20yet%20journalists%20across%20the%20world%20find%20themselves%20behind%20bars.%20In%202023%2C%20Israel%20emerged%20as%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20leading%20jailers%20of%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20India%2C%20too%2C%20has%20a%20tarnished%20record.%20According%20to%20data%20just%20released%20by%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%2C%20seven%20media%20persons%20remain%20in%20prison.%20India%20continues%20to%20draw%20criticism%20over%20the%20use%20of%20security%20laws%20including%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20and%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20to%20silence%20the%20media.%20Five%20of%20seven%20journalists%20are%20being%20investigated%20under%2Fcharged%20under%20terrorism-related%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA).%20Three%20journalists%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20census%20have%20been%20released%20on%20bail%2C%20while%20three%20new%20journalists%20have%20been%20arrested%20since%20then.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EThe%207%20Imprisoned%20journalists%20in%20India%20as%20of%20December%201%2C%202023%20are%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1)%20Aasif%20Sultan%2C%20Kashmir%20Narrator%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(since%20August%2027%2C%202018%20%E2%80%93%205%20years%203%20months)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Faasif-sultan%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Faasif-sultan%2F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2)%20Gautam%20Navlakha%2C%20Freelance%20journalist%2C%20Maharashtra%20(since%20April%2014%2C%202020%20%E2%80%93%203%20year%2C%207%20months)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Fgautam-navlakha%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Fgautam-navlakha%2F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3)%20Sajad%20Gul%2C%20The%20Kashmir%20Walla%2C%C2%A0%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(since%20January%2005%2C%202022%20%E2%80%93%201%20year%2011%20months)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Fsajad-gul%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Fsajad-gul%2F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4)%20Rupesh%20Kumar%20Singh%2C%20Freelance%20journalist%2C%20Jharkhand%20(since%20July%2017%2C%202022%20%E2%80%93%201%20year%205%20months)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Frupesh-kumar-singh%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Fdata%2Fpeople%2Frupesh-kumar-singh%2F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5)%C2%A0Prabir%20Purkayasth